<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[94,718,1562,1715]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,360,1562,1587]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Constantin, 2020" authorityName="Constantin" authorityYear="2020" box="[368,595,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[368,595,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Plectonotum luteipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[602,691,1562,1587]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1988" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1988" box="[201,428,1594,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis box="[201,267,1594,1619]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P.inca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[271,428,1594,1619]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="325 - 341" refId="ref19826" refString="Wittmer, W. 1988. 40. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Fauna (Coleoptera, Cantharidae und Malachiidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 12: 325 - 341." type="journal article" year="1988">Wittmer, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by the similar habitus, colour pattern and pronotal shape. It differs from the latter by the longer pronotal bead, the darker legs and the different aedeagus shape.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
